review_blob: I tried this beer back in 2007. I was working at village bottle shop and my manager broke the neck off one of the 4 bottles we had on accident. The break was perfect. None of the beer spilled and it didnt get into the beer. I poured the remaining into a nalgene bottle and saved it until I got home for a more proper tasting. I like this beer because they are pushing the envelope and just the idea of what beer is and can be. No head at all completely no carbonation. Lots of molasses and caramelized sugars. Alcohol presence heavy, very very warming. It would make for a nice beer to enjoy during the heart of winter with good friends.

Best example of a harvest ale that I have tried. Drink this beer as soon as possible. Do not store it for any amount of time. This is a fresh beer So DRINK IT! Its so fresh its almost oily. You can almost taste the freshy released alpha acid. MMM Citrus, grapefruit, hints of lime. Great beer again. Long live founders
2 finger head. I love that it comes in a can. I couldnt see a fishing or camping trip complete without this beer or dales pale ale. Good beer equals better times!
Good beer. I like the different style. Sweet stout with a creamy head. Caramel with a hint of molasses sweetness. Worth trying. Left hand is a good brew co.
beer_name: Left Hand Fade To Black Vol. 1: Foreign Stout

review_blob: This has become my favorite porter. This beer a true golden example of what porters should be. Pours a small dark brown head with a very very dark brown body. The flavors of dark chocolate, coffee, and toffee. Its a beautiful beer by one of my favorite breweries. Great great job guys.

Small frothy white head pours to a sparkling ruby body. Burnt straw. Harsh hops of pine,spruce, and grapefruit that die out to a very long lasting bitter in your mouth. It was a good example of an Imperial ESB. Im glad to see breweries are keeping esbs alive.
Nice belgian style from north coast. Floral nose. You get a little sour on the taste from the yeast strains. Nice looking beer, yellow-orange medium body beer. Its worth trying if you come across it.

I cant believe this beer got such a high rating? Pours a creamy frothy light brown mocha 3 finger head. Dark roasted coffee on the nose. The body was alot lighter then I like with a porter. Light flavors. It would make a nice early evening beer perhaps a warm up for a beer tasting.

Nice abbey style. I drank it around 50 degrees F. and was happy with the flavors I got from that. It could be drank a little warmer perhaps. It pours a lively a head that is medium lasting with a sparkling ruby body. Malty, floral nose with hints of bread. Cherry flavors with light to medium alcohol presence. Another step on the beer-a-myd!

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Drank out of a tulip and a snifter. Huge head that lasted for ever. Light flowers and yeast on the nose. Medium to heavy on the hops balanced very well with malty sweetness. This is the golden example of a golden ale. Great beer brewed in honor of Fred.
Great beer! 2 finger creamy frothy head that last. Lots of pineapple, citrus, grapefruit with hints of lemon and lime. very well balanced beer with a great nose. Good job once again bells.
